<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Boer&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">
<div class="mw-references-wrap"><ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Afrikaans is a daughter language of Dutch; see <a href="#CITEREFBooij1999">Booij 1999</a>, p.&#160;2, <a href="#CITEREFJansenSchreuderNeijt2007">Jansen, Schreuder &amp; Neijt 2007</a>, p.&#160;5, <a href="#CITEREFMennenLeveltGerrits2006">Mennen, Levelt &amp; Gerrits 2006</a>, p.&#160;1, <a href="#CITEREFBooij2003">Booij 2003</a>, p.&#160;4, <a href="#CITEREFHiskensAuerKerswill2005">Hiskens, Auer &amp; Kerswill 2005</a>, p.&#160;19, <a href="#CITEREFHeeringade_Wet2007">Heeringa &amp; de Wet 2007</a>, pp.&#160;1, 3, 5.<br />Afrikaans was historically called Cape Dutch; see <a href="#CITEREFDeumertVandenbussche2003">Deumert &amp; Vandenbussche 2003</a>, p.&#160;16, <a href="#CITEREFConradie2005">Conradie 2005</a>, p.&#160;208, <a href="#CITEREFSebba1997">Sebba 1997</a>, p.&#160;160, <a href="#CITEREFLangerDavies2005">Langer &amp; Davies 2005</a>, p.&#160;144, <a href="#CITEREFDeumert2002">Deumert 2002</a>, p.&#160;3, <a href="#CITEREFBerdichevsky2004">Berdichevsky 2004</a>, p.&#160;130.<br />Afrikaans is rooted in seventeenth century dialects of Dutch; see <a href="#CITEREFHolm1989">Holm 1989</a>, p.&#160;338, <a href="#CITEREFGeertsClyne1992">Geerts &amp; Clyne 1992</a>, p.&#160;71, <a href="#CITEREFMesthrie1995">Mesthrie 1995</a>, p.&#160;214, <a href="#CITEREFNieslerLouwRoux2005">Niesler, Louw &amp; Roux 2005</a>, p.&#160;459.<br />Afrikaans is variously described as a <a href="/wiki/Creole_language" title="Creole language">creole</a>, a partially creolised language, or a deviant variety of Dutch; see <a href="#CITEREFSebba2007">Sebba 2007</a>, p.&#160;116.</span>
</li>
</ol></div></div>
